Terna Denies Report of Possible Merger With Snam Rete Gas

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-04-14T13:00:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/terna-denies-report-of-possible-merger-with-snam-rete-gas.html
Terna SpA,  Italy ’s power network
operator, denied a report that it’s planning a merger with  Snam
Rete Gas SpA (SRG) , the owner of the natural-gas grid.  The two companies are not in talks over a possible
combination, an official from Terna said. He was responding to a
report in La Repubblica that Terna, Snam, Italy’s  Finance
Ministry , and State lender Cassa Depositi e Prestiti SpA had
held meetings to discuss a possible merger between the two.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandra Migliaccio in Rome at 
 amigliaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  